  "response": "Here are some tips to improve at witty comebacks:\n\n1. Practice quick thinking\n- Develop mental agility\n- Learn to think on your feet\n\n2. Study comedians and witty people\n- Watch stand-up comedy\n- Observe clever dialogue in movies/shows\n- Analyze their timing and delivery\n\n3. Learn different types of humor\n- Wordplay\n- Sarcasm\n- Self-deprecating humor\n- Observational comedy\n\n4. Develop your timing\n- Practice delivering lines with confidence\n- Work on your comedic pause and rhythm\n\n5. Read and expand your vocabulary\n- A rich vocabulary helps create clever wordplay\n- Learn puns and linguistic tricks\n\n6. Listen actively during conversations\n- Pay attention to context\n- Find opportunities for clever responses\n\n7. Don't force it\n- Natural, spontaneous wit is more effective\n- Be genuine and authentic\n\n8. Practice improvisation\n- Take improv classes\n- Play verbal sparring games with friends\n\n9. Know when to be serious\n- Not every situation requires a witty comeback\n- Understand appropriate social contexts\n\n10. Stay confident and relaxed\n- Delivery matters as much as the line itself\n- Confidence makes comebacks more effective",
